HEADWORD: Pedage
<hw>Ped"age</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧d"⟦asl⟧j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>pedagium</ets>, for <ets>pedaticum</ets>. See
<er>Paage</er>.]</ety> <def>A toll or tax paid by passengers, entitling
them to safe-conduct and protection.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spelman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

